allocatedStorage.description: Specifies the allocated storage size in gigabytes (GB).

availabilityZone.description: Specifies the name of the Availability Zone the DB instance was located in at the time of the DB snapshot.

dbInstanceIdentifier.description: The DB Instance Identifier from which to take the snapshot.

dbSnapshotArn.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the DB snapshot.

encrypted.description: Specifies whether the DB snapshot is encrypted.

engine.description: Specifies the name of the database engine.

engineVersion.description: Specifies the version of the database engine.

iops.description: Specifies the Provisioned IOPS (I/O operations per second) value of the DB instance at the time of the snapshot.

kmsKeyId.description: The ARN for the KMS encryption key.

licenseModel.description: License model information for the restored DB instance.

optionGroupName.description: Provides the option group name for the DB snapshot.

sharedAccounts.description: List of AWS Account ids to share snapshot with, use `all` to make snaphot public.

sourceDbSnapshotIdentifier.description: The DB snapshot Arn that the DB snapshot was copied from. It only has value in case of cross customer or cross region copy.

sourceRegion.description: The region that the DB snapshot was created in or copied from.

status.description: Specifies the status of this DB snapshot.

storageType.description: Specifies the storage type associated with DB snapshot.

tagsAll.description: A map of tags assigned to the resource, including those inherited from the provider `default_tags` configuration block.
